  "doc_id": "51091",
  "text": "TiC-Mo 2 C-Ni cermets were produced at the Powder Metallurgy Laboratory, Tallinn University of Technology by means of a conventional powder metallurgy routine described elsewhere [CITATION_1] . The chemical composition of initial powders, the density and mechanical properties of cermets tested are summarized in Table 1 and also described in [CITATION_2] . Density of the materials was measured using the Archimedes approach. Transverse rupture strength was determined in the 3-point bending test arrangement. Palmqvist method was applied for fracture toughness evaluation.",
